VALUES
(41, 3, 22, 41, 7, 1, 1, NULL, 'Connection of Scribes from Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of scribes from Jerusalem. The first mentions their accusation against Jesus, while the second highlights their gathering to confront him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 22, 42, 11, 15, 15, 'He hath Beelzebub', 'Accusation of Beelzebub', 'Both passages emphasize the accusation that Jesus casts out demons by Beelzebub, linking the two accounts. This connection highlights the consistent challenge Jesus faced from religious authorities regarding his miraculous works.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 22, 43, 8, 48, 48, NULL, 'Accusations of Demonic Influence', 'Both passages emphasize accusations against Jesus regarding demonic possession. In Mark, He is called Beelzebub, while in John, He is accused of having a devil.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 22, 19, 22, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Reproach and Despising', 'This connection highlights the theme of being despised and rejected. In Mark, Jesus is accused of being associated with evil, while in Psalms, the speaker expresses being a reproach and despised by people.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 23, 40, 12, 25, 30, 'Satan cast out Satan', 'Connection of Divided Kingdoms', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of division within a kingdom. Mark 3:23 poses the question of how Satan can cast out Satan, while Matthew 12:25-30 elaborates on this idea, stating that a divided kingdom cannot stand. This thematic link underscores the impossibility of internal conflict within Satan''s realm.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 23, 42, 11, 17, 23, 'Satan cast out Satan', 'Unity Against Division', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that a divided kingdom cannot stand, highlighting the absurdity of Satan casting out Satan. This connection illustrates the broader theme of unity versus division in the context of spiritual authority.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 23, 40, 13, 34, 34, 'in parables', 'Connection of Parables in Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the use of parables in Jesus'' teaching. Mark highlights the questioning of authority through parables, while Matthew notes that Jesus exclusively used parables to communicate with the multitude.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 23, 41, 4, 2, 2, 'in parables', 'Connection through Parables', 'Both passages emphasize the use of parables in teaching. In Mark 3:23, Jesus uses parables to illustrate a point about Satan, while Mark 4:2 highlights his broader teaching method of using parables.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 23, 19, 49, 4, 4, 'in parables', 'Connection of Parables and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the use of parables to convey deeper meanings. Mark 3:23 questions the logic of division within evil, while Psalms 49:4 expresses a desire to understand a parable, suggesting a pursuit of wisdom through metaphor.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 24, 38, 11, 14, 14, 'a kingdom be divided against itself', 'Division and Brotherhood', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of division. Mark highlights that a divided kingdom cannot stand, while Zechariah illustrates the breaking of brotherhood between Judah and Israel, suggesting that division leads to downfall.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 24, 10, 20, 1, 1, 'a kingdom be divided against itself', 'Division and Its Consequences', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of division. Mark highlights that a divided kingdom cannot stand, while 2 Samuel illustrates a division within Israel as Sheba calls for separation from David. This connection highlights the theme of unity versus division.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 24, 23, 19, 2, 3, 'a kingdom be divided against itself', 'Division and Conflict in Kingdoms', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of internal division within a kingdom. Mark highlights that a divided kingdom cannot stand, while Isaiah depicts Egyptians fighting against each other, illustrating the destructive nature of such division.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 24, 26, 37, 22, 22, 'divided against itself', 'Unity and Division in Kingdoms', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of unity versus division within kingdoms. Mark highlights that a divided kingdom cannot stand, while Ezekiel prophesies the unification of Israel into one nation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 24, 46, 1, 10, 13, 'a kingdom be divided against itself', 'Divisions and Unity in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of divisions, with Mark stating that a divided kingdom cannot stand, while Paul urges unity among believers to avoid contentions. This connection highlights the importance of collective harmony in the faith community.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 24, 7, 9, 23, 57, 'a kingdom be divided against itself', 'Division Leading to Destruction', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of division within a group. In Mark, a divided kingdom cannot stand, while in Judges, the treachery among Abimelech and the men of Shechem leads to their downfall.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 24, 7, 12, 1, 6, 'a kingdom be divided against itself', 'Division and Conflict', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of internal division. In Mark, a divided kingdom cannot stand, while in Judges, the conflict between Gilead and Ephraim leads to destruction and loss. This connection highlights the destructive nature of discord within a community.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 25, 59, 3, 16, 16, 'divided against itself', 'Division and Disorder', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of division and conflict. Mark 3:25 speaks to the inability of a divided house to stand, while James 3:16 highlights that strife leads to confusion and evil. This connection highlights the destructive nature of discord.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 25, 48, 5, 15, 15, 'divided against itself', 'Division and Conflict in Community', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of internal conflict. Mark highlights that a divided house cannot stand, while Galatians warns against biting and devouring one another, suggesting that such behavior leads to destruction.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 25, 19, 133, 1, 1, NULL, 'Unity and Division in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the importance of unity among brethren, as seen in Psalms 133:1, which celebrates harmonious relationships. In contrast, Mark 3:25 warns that division leads to failure, emphasizing that a lack of unity undermines stability.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 25, 1, 37, 4, 4, 'a house be divided against itself', 'Divided Relationships and Consequences', 'This connection highlights the theme of division within relationships. In Mark 3:25, the idea of a house divided suggests that internal conflict leads to downfall, which is mirrored in Genesis 37:4, where Joseph''s brothers'' hatred creates division in their family.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 25, 1, 13, 7, 8, 'divided against itself', 'Divided House and Strife', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of unity. Mark highlights that a divided house cannot stand, while Genesis illustrates the need to resolve strife between brethren to maintain harmony.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 27, 23, 49, 24, 26, 'strong man''s house', 'Deliverance from the Mighty', 'This connection highlights the theme of overcoming a strong adversary. Both passages emphasize the ability to rescue captives from a powerful oppressor, illustrating God''s power to bind the strong and deliver the prey.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 27, 40, 12, 29, 29, 'bind the strong man', 'Connection of Strong Man Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of binding the strong man before spoiling his house. This parallel structure highlights the necessity of overcoming the strong man to access his goods.', 'parallel', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 27, 42, 11, 21, 23, 'strong man', 'Connection of Strong Man Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a ''strong man'' whose goods can only be taken by a stronger force. This connection highlights the idea of overcoming opposition to achieve victory.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 27, 49, 6, 10, 13, 'strong man', 'Strength and Spiritual Warfare', 'This connection highlights the theme of strength in both passages. Mark discusses binding the strong man, while Ephesians emphasizes being strong in the Lord to withstand spiritual forces.', 'theme', 0.391, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 27, 66, 20, 1, 3, 'bind the strong man', 'Binding the Strong Man', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of binding a powerful adversary before achieving victory. In Mark, the strong man must be bound to spoil his house, while in Revelation, Satan is bound for a thousand years to prevent his deception.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 27, 23, 53, 12, 12, 'spoil his house', 'Binding and Spoiling Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of binding the strong man to spoil his house, which parallels the idea of dividing the spoil with the strong in Isaiah. Both passages emphasize the concept of overcoming a powerful adversary to claim victory and share in the spoils.', 'theme', 0.37, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 27, 62, 4, 4, 4, 'strong man', 'Overcoming the Strong Man', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of overcoming a powerful adversary. In Mark, the strong man represents a formidable force that must be bound, while in 1 John, the greater power within believers signifies their victory over worldly challenges.', 'theme', 0.37, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 28, 42, 12, 10, 10, 'blasphemies wherewith soever they shall blaspheme', 'Forgiveness and Blasphemy Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of forgiveness for sins and blasphemies, while highlighting a specific exception regarding blasphemy against the Holy Spirit. This connection underscores the seriousness of blasphemy in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 28, 40, 12, 31, 32, 'blasphemies wherewith soever they shall blaspheme', 'Forgiveness and Blasphemy Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of forgiveness for sins and blasphemies, while highlighting the unique severity of blasphemy against the Holy Spirit. This connection underscores the distinction made regarding the unforgivable nature of such blasphemy.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
